Ah, I see what‚Äôs happening. Your Apache and Postfix/Dovecot services are running, but Cloudflare is giving a 523 ‚ÄúOrigin is unreachable‚Äù error, which means that even though the services are up on your VPS, Cloudflare cannot reach your server from the public internet. This is not about Postfix/Dovecot being offline‚Äîit‚Äôs a networking/DNS issue.

Here‚Äôs how to troubleshoot and fix it step by step:

1Ô∏è‚É£ Check your DNS settings in Cloudflare
Log in to Cloudflare.

Go to DNS for your domain zovenax.com.

Look for the A record for mail.zovenax.com.

Make sure the IP matches your VPS‚Äôs public IP (not internal IP).

Make sure the Cloud icon is orange if using proxy, or gray if you want direct access (for mail, gray/‚ÄúDNS only‚Äù is recommended).

2Ô∏è‚É£ Check if your server‚Äôs firewall allows Cloudflare
Cloudflare uses specific IP ranges. If your VPS firewall blocks them, Cloudflare cannot reach your server.

For testing, you can temporarily disable UFW:

sudo ufw disable
Or allow HTTP/HTTPS (80, 443) from all:

sudo ufw allow 80,443/tcp
sudo ufw reload
3Ô∏è‚É£ Check if your server is listening on the right ports
On your server, check Apache:

sudo lsof -i :80
sudo lsof -i :443
You should see Apache LISTENING on 0.0.0.0:80 and 0.0.0.0:443.

If it‚Äôs correct, try curl from outside:

curl -I http://mail.zovenax.com
4Ô∏è‚É£ Ensure Apache is configured for your domain
In /etc/apache2/sites-available/, make sure your VirtualHost exists for mail.zovenax.com. Example:

<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName mail.zovenax.com
    DocumentRoot /var/www/html
</VirtualHost>
Then enable it:

sudo a2ensite mail.zovenax.com.conf
sudo systemctl reload apache2
5Ô∏è‚É£ Check for NAT / ISP / VPS issues
Sometimes VPS providers block ports 80/443, or Cloudflare cannot reach your IP.

Confirm your public IP: curl ifconfig.me

Confirm Cloudflare is pointing to exact same IP.

üí° Important: For email (Postfix/Dovecot), do not proxy through Cloudflare‚Äîset DNS to gray cloud (DNS only) for MX records. Cloudflare proxy only works for web traffic.

