Make sure it points exactly to 161.118.169.180.

For mail subdomains, turn off proxy (gray cloud) so Cloudflare doesn‚Äôt proxy mail ports.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Apache is only listening on IPv6
netstat shows tcp6 :::80 LISTEN.

This means it listens only on IPv6. Some networks may not reach it via IPv4.

To force Apache to listen on IPv4, edit /etc/apache2/ports.conf:

sudo nano /etc/apache2/ports.conf
Make sure it has:

Listen 80
Listen [::]:80
Then restart Apache:

sudo systemctl restart apache2
3Ô∏è‚É£ Install ping/telnet for connectivity tests
sudo apt update
sudo apt install iputils-ping telnet -y
Then you can test:

ping mail.zovenax.com
telnet mail.zovenax.com 80
4Ô∏è‚É£ VPS provider restrictions
Some cloud providers block HTTP/SMTP ports by default.

If after steps 1‚Äì3, you still can‚Äôt reach port 80 from outside, check your VPS provider‚Äôs network/firewall panel.

